			<div type="transcription">
				<div type="original">
					<p>The original transcription is not available.</p>
				</div>
				<div type="translation">
					<pb facs="R 6457-71 (16)" n="1"/>
					<p><!--Alexander Kirk, (Telegramm), Berlin, 1.8.1940, Teil 1, S. 1, Teil 2, S. 1 Records of the Department of State relating to internal affairs of Poland 1916-1944, Washington 1981 (Mikrofilm-Edition): Dokument 860C.4016/617.--></p>
					<p>The following information with regard to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">deportation</term> of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> from <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/3094802/krakow.html">Krakow</placeName> was furnished in confidence by <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-892" type="subject">Jewish leaders</term> at <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/maps/google_52.23_21.012.html">Warsaw</placeName>. <pb facs="R 6457-71 (17)" n="2"/> The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jewish population</term> of <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/3094802/krakow.html">Krakow</placeName> now totals some 67,000 including about 11,000 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-519" type="subject">deportees</term> who have recently arrived from <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Polish</placeName> regions annexed to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Germany</placeName>. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518"
							type="subject">deportation</term> held in <date when="1940-05">May</date> will immediately affect a total of 80,000 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> and it cannot be regarded otherwise than a major disaster to
							<term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_poles">Polish</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jewry</term>. The break up of the ancient, rich and powerful <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-872" type="subject">Jewish community</term> at <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/3094802/krakow.html">Krakow</placeName> can bring nothing but <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-848" type="subject">destitution</term> to its members who will be forced on short notice to <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-880" type="subject">emigrate</term> without resources to such localities in the <ref target="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/admin/keywords/ehri_terms-1191">General Government</ref> as are able and willing to receive
						them.</p>
